l coaches to <strong>GoPro&#8217;s own video producers have enjoyed Highlight Hunter&#8217;s incredibly simple 3-step process</strong>:</p><p>1. Record with your camera as usual. After something cool happens, cover the lens with your hand for 1 second.<br /> 2. Sit back and relax while Highlight Hunter scans your videos for the highlights you marked.<br /> 3. Share the best highlights on Facebook, save them as videos, or open them in your favorite video editor.</p><p>&#8220;Sharing the best moments from your favorite activities just got easier and a lot more fun,&#8221; said Noah Spitzer-Williams, CEO of Highlight Hunter. &#8220;The product has proven itself to be hugely beneficial and the support of GoPro has really energized our team.”</p><p>Highlight Hunter cuts video editing time down by over 80%, making it easy to create and share quality highlights.  It&#8217;s <strong>completely free for the at-home user</strong>, while professional video editors and content creators can unlock powerful features by upgrading to Highlight Hunter Pro — export videos in ProRes format, save videos without tiny watermarks, and open highlights directly in popular video editing software.</p><p>In addition to GoPro owners, many others have embraced Highlight Hunter. Exciting and unexpected moments happen all the time — a child’s first steps, soccer games, school plays, the list goes on and on. With Highlight Hunter, sharing highlights is quick and easy, and users from all walks of life are taking advantage.</p><div class="one_third"> <a href="../static2.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-tutorial.png" class="lightbox"><br /> <img src="../static1.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-tutorial-250w.png" alt="Tutorial"/><br /> </a></div><div class="one_third"> <a href="../static1.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-select-videos-empty.png" class="lightbox"><br /> <img src="../static1.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-select-videos-empty-250w.png" alt="Select Videos from Camera"/><br /> </a></div><div class="one_third last"> <a href="../static1.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-details.png" class="lightbox"><br /> <img src="../static4.highlighthunter.com/images/press-kit/screenshot-details-250w.png" alt="Highlight Details"/><br /> </a></div><p><br/><br/>&nbsp;<br/></p><p><strong>About Highlight Hunter</strong></p><p>Based in Seattle, Washington, Highlight Hunter grew out of a passion for extreme sports. The team realized people needed an easier way to quickly create highlight reels, and developed an app to solve the problem. Highlight Hunter is available at <a href="index.html" >www.highlighthunter.com</a>, completely free for the at-home version. Professional video editors and content creators can unlock powerful features by upgrading to Highlight Hunter Pro for $99.</p><p>Press Contact<br /> Matt Mormino<br /> <a href="mailto:matt@highlighthunter.com">matt@highlighthunter.com</a><br /> Press Kit: <a href="press-kit" >www.highlighthunter.com/press-kit</a><br /> <a href="index.html" >www.highlighthunter.com</a></p></div><br class="clear"/></div></div></div><div class="bottom_shadow"></div><div id="footer"><div id="footer_shadow"></div><ul class="sidebar_widget"></ul> <br class="clear"/><div id="copyright"><div class="standard_wrapper" style="text-shadow: 0 1px #000;"><div style="float:right"> <a href="http://www.twitter.com/highlighthunter" class="tipsy" title="Twitter"> <img src="../static2.highlighthunter.com/wp-content/themes/Lotus/images/about_icon/twitter.png"/> </a> <a href="http://www.facebook.com/HighlightHunter" class="tipsy" title="Facebook"> <img src="../static1.highlighthunter.com/wp-content/themes/Lotus/images/about_icon/facebook.png"/> </a></div><div style="float:left;" align="left"> <a href="contact/index.html">Contact Us</a> • <a href="about-us/index.html">About the Team</a> • <a href="press-kit">Press Kit</a> • <a href="press-release-v2-pc">Press Release</a> • <a href="